
[1]beguile

   BEGUI'LE, v.t. begi'le. [be and guile.] To delude; to deceive; to
   impose on by artifice or craft.

   The serpent beguiled me and I did eat Gen.3.

   1. To elude by craft.

   When misery could beguile the tyrant's rage.

   2. To elude any thing disagreeable by amusement, or other means; to
   pass pleasingly; to amuse; as, to beguile the tedious day with sleep.
